. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M." box="[467,673,1572,1598]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" pagination="564 - 568" refId="ref102695" refString="Bezzi, M. (1907) Leptidae et Empididae in Insula Formosa a clar. H. Sauter collectae. Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 5, 564 - 568." type="journal article" year="1907">Bezzi (1907: 566</bibRefCitation>
, female only) described this species from material (without indication of number of specimens studied) taken by H. Sauter from Takao. Later, he (1912) examined numerous specimens, including males, of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Quate" authorityYear="1960" box="[527,670,1652,1677]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosae">
<emphasis box="[527,670,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">E. formosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Takao, 
<collectingRegion box="[833,912,1651,1677]" country="Taiwan" name="Tainan" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">Tainan</collectingRegion>
and Polisha. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M." box="[1076,1229,1651,1677]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" pagination="65 - 78" refId="ref102761" refString="Bezzi, M. (1914) H. Sauter's Formosa-Ausbeute. Rhagionidae et Empididae. Supplementa Entomologica, Berlin, 3, 65 - 78." type="journal article" year="1914">Bezzi (1914)</bibRefCitation>
noted 
<specimenCount pageId="135" pageNumber="136" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Quate" authorityYear="1960" box="[252,394,1691,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosae">
<emphasis box="[252,394,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">E. formosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that he found in the 
<collectionCode box="[640,689,1691,1717]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33211" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33211" name="Senckenberg Deutsches Entomologisches Institut" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" type="Other type of research institution/biorepository">DEI</collectionCode>
Collection (see above). The type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Quate" authorityYear="1960" box="[1120,1262,1691,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosae">
<emphasis box="[1120,1262,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">E. formosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was deposited in the Hungarian Museum (Budapest) and it was destroyed in 1956 (Papp and Földvári, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="135.[151,1437,151,2034]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">
